      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Related to #2334 \r\n\r\n`flash_attn/cute/logging.py` has the same name as Python's stdlib logging module.   \r\n\r\nWhen we run `pip install -e`, setuptools adds the package source directory (`flash_attn/cute/`) to sys.path. Then when setuptools internally does import logging (which it needs for its own setup), Python finds `flash_attn/cute/logging.py` first instead of the stdlib one. That local file in turn does import `cutlass.cute`, which eventually calls logging.getLogger(...).\r\n\r\nBut the stdlib logging module hasn't finished initializing yet (since we hijacked its import), causing the AttributeError: partially initialized module circular import crash.\r\n\r\nThe fix is simply renaming logging.py → fa_logging.py so it no longer shadows the stdlib module. The only place that imports it is interface.py:\r\n                                                                                                                                     \r\n```python                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \r\n# before                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           \r\nfrom flash_attn.cute import logging as fa_logging                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              \r\n# after                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \r\nfrom flash_attn.cute import fa_logging\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2026-03-12T05:59:27Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-12T14:52:50Z",
